contextItems.content:
```src/css/Style.css
/* Theme Variables */
:root {
  --primary-bg: #1a1a1a;
  --primary-text: #ffffff;
  --accent-color: #00ff00;
}

[data-theme="light"] {
  --primary-bg: #ffffff;
  --primary-text: #1a1a1a;
  --accent-color: #00cc00;
}

/* Base Styles */
body {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 20px;
  background-color: var(--primary-bg);
  color: var(--primary-text);
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.6;
  max-width: 800px;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

/* Theme Toggle */
.theme-toggle {
  position: fixed;
  top: 20px;
  right: 20px;
  padding: 10px;
  background-color: var(--accent-color);
  border: none;
  color: white;
  cursor: pointer;
  border-radius: 5px;
}

.theme-toggle:hover {
  opacity: 0.9;
}

/* Content Styles */
.content {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 20px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

h1, h2, h3 {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

h1 {
  font-size: 2.5em;
  color: var(--accent-color);
}

h2 {
  font-size: 2em;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent-color);
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

section {
  margin: 2rem 0;
  padding: 1rem;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
}

/* Responsive Design */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    padding: 10px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2em;
  }

  section {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
}
```

message.content:
The issue seems to be related to how the container width and padding are handled in your CSS. Here's a solution:

```css src/css/Style.css
/* ... existing code ... */

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    padding: 10px;
    max-width: 100%; /* Change from fixed pixel value */
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2em;
  }

  section {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.5rem; /* Use smaller margins and padding */
  }

  .content {
    width: calc(100% - 20px); /* Adjust for side margins if needed */
  }

  img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
}
```

Key changes:
1. Removed fixed `max-width` at mobile breakpoint
2. Used percentage-based widths instead of fixed pixels
3. Added specific handling for images to maintain aspect ratio
4. Simplified the selector hierarchy for better responsiveness

This should make your text fill the available width more gracefully while maintaining proper spacing and proportions.
